title: Tech
description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from Tech, skipping any feeds with errors.

items.title: India’s gig workers win legal status, but access to social security remains elusive
items.description: India is restructuring its gig economy with a new labor law, but much more is needed before gig workers see real benefits.

items.title: Google teams up with Accel to hunt for India’s next AI breakouts
items.description: Google and Accel will jointly invest up to $2 million in each startup through their new partnership.

items.title: Anthropic releases Opus 4.5 with new Chrome and Excel integrations
items.description: Anthropic has launched Opus 4.5, the latest version of its flagship model, with new integrations into Chrome and Excel.

items.title: OpenAI learned the hard way that Cameo trademarked the word ‘cameo’
items.description: OpenAI might have to rename the "cameo" feature in the Sora app.

items.title: AWS is spending $50B build AI infrastructure for the US government
items.description: AWS has been working with the U.S. government since 2011 and is now building AI infrastructure specifically for the entity.
